Art of India and Southeast Asia
Harry N. Abrams | 1971 | ISBN: 0810980134 | English | 270 pages | PDF | 38.2 MB


The arts of the lndian subcontinent and of those surrounding lands that fell under its artistic influence are core given an unrivaled pictorial treatment. The splendid illustrations and informative text of this book carry the story from the earliest evidence of civilization at such sites as Mohenjo-Daro and Harappa in the third millennium b.c. to the exquisite products of the Rajput and Pahari schools of miniature painting of about a hundred years ago
